1
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:39,070
[A Love Never Lost]

2
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,880
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:43,229 --> 00:01:44,400
Mr. Kanyama.

4
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:46,200
You're pretty.

5
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:49,229
Prettier than before.

6
00:01:50,479 --> 00:01:51,610
Where have you been?

7
00:01:51,789 --> 00:01:52,560
My brother-in-law

8
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,200
insisted I go to Utako Shimoda's school

9
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,330
to study for a while.

10
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,479
Utako Shimoda?

11
00:01:58,340 --> 00:01:59,979
She's a noble lady in Tokyo.

12
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,430
How's business

13
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:04,040
been lately,

14
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,000
Mr. Kanyama?

15
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:07,120
Not great.

16
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:09,710
It's slack.

17
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:14,090
Even the paintings
haven't been selling since you left.

18
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:19,840
Mr. Wu asked me to bring this to you.

19
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,210
Here's the thing, Shuhong.

20
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,240
I checked out the place Mr. Wu mentioned.

21
00:02:27,870 --> 00:02:29,430
It's a nice location.

22
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,970
There's a bakery
right by the street downstairs.

23
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,290
You can consider

24
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:37,360
renting that shop.

25
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,870
Will they agree?

26
00:02:40,290 --> 00:02:42,690
The bakery downstairs is doing quite well.

27
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,800
I'll make them agree.

28
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,720
I'll open another bakery?

29
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,630
No, no, no.

30
00:02:50,310 --> 00:02:51,370
A stationery shop.

31
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:53,360
To help me with distribution.

32
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,360
What do you think?

33
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:57,590
It keeps things discreet and convenient,

34
00:02:57,590 --> 00:02:58,310
doesn't it?

35
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,240
About the costs,

36
00:03:01,310 --> 00:03:02,870
we can sign

37
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:04,200
an agreement right now.

38
00:03:06,710 --> 00:03:07,430
Yes.

39
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,240
Right, this is it.

40
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,750
[Agreement]

41
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:38,310
What are you writing?

42
00:03:38,310 --> 00:03:38,710
Go away.

43
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:39,240
For…

44
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:42,020
All private matters. Stop snooping.

45
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:43,150
What?

46
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,560
I think you're out of your mind.

47
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,280
You really don't

48
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,760
learn your lesson, do you?

49
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,800
So what?

50
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,680
By the way,

51
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:54,960
don't tell Liang Xiang about this.

52
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:57,560
Why not? You're afraid of him?

53
00:03:58,310 --> 00:03:59,710
I'm not afraid of anyone.

54
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:01,410
I'm just afraid

55
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:03,120
he'll nag me like you.

56
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:11,310
Never figured you

57
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,280
for the gutsy type.

58
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,800
Have you heard this poem?

59
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:18,680
What poem?

60
00:04:19,630 --> 00:04:21,360
"With a smile, I walk this road.

61
00:04:21,769 --> 00:04:24,630
With a smile,
I walk through the heart of the desert.

62
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:26,780
Where is the place I'll finally rest?"

63
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:28,720
Where?

64
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,750
"I'll be buried by unfamiliar hands

65
00:04:31,870 --> 00:04:34,040
in the barren desert."

66
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,680
How tragic.

67
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,830
"With a smile, I walk this road.

68
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:41,159
I keep walking,

69
00:04:41,159 --> 00:04:43,600
walking toward where I want to be."

70
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:47,720
You mean hell?

71
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,159
You're hopeless.

72
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:52,430
What road, Kaizhi?

73
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,690
Where are you going?

74
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,120
I was joking with Qianli.

75
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:01,280
We're still on rotating patrol tonight.

76
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,940
The password is "curry rice."

77
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,720
Sounds delicious.

78
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,190
I've only heard of it in passwords.

79
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:09,040
The canteen never serves curry rice.

80
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:11,240
It's always carrot stew with potatoes.

81
00:05:11,450 --> 00:05:13,190
Kaizhi, you're on first watch tonight.

82
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:14,190
Go to the post now.

83
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,310
Be on time for the changeover.

84
00:05:27,310 --> 00:05:28,310
Don't oversleep.

85
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:30,720
Don't worry.

86
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:41,050
[Tea]

87
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,310
You're not still tangled up

88
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,159
with that Korean girl,

89
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:53,270
are you?

90
00:05:54,430 --> 00:05:55,159
Cut it out.

91
00:05:55,780 --> 00:05:57,380
I really don't have the time.

92
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:59,360
I've got several exams waiting for me.

93
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,190
No time to teach for you.

94
00:06:02,310 --> 00:06:03,190
I don't get it.

95
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:05,290
It's only a handful of you.

96
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:07,040
Why the need for a military school?

97
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,160
It's not my idea.

98
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:09,830
Sun Wen asked me for help.

99
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,480
He's starting the Qingshan Military School

100
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,610
and asked me to find a few instructors.

101
00:06:14,830 --> 00:06:15,480
Aren't we

102
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,000
discussing a merger?

103
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:20,120
Shouldn't you show some goodwill?

104
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:23,050
I really can't spare the time.

105
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:24,610
Fine.

106
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,890
How's Liang Xiang been lately?

107
00:06:29,030 --> 00:06:29,960
Whatever you do,

108
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:31,430
you have to

109
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:32,600
win him over for me.

110
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:36,060
He left a great first impression.

111
00:06:36,310 --> 00:06:37,390
I have a feeling—

112
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,130
this guy's a real talent.

113
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:40,000
Of course.

114
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,120
Li Renjun told me

115
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,220
Yuan Shikai

116
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:44,750
personally saved a regimental commander post

117
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:45,750
for him.

118
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,390
He's determined to win him over.

119
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:49,310
Yuan Shikai's making quiet moves too,

120
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:50,310
placing pawns in advance.

121
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:51,750
Liang Xiang's no pawn.

122
00:06:52,430 --> 00:06:53,600
He's very popular.

123
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,120
When we left Shanghai,

124
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:59,390
Prince Chun, Zaifeng, personally met him.

125
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:00,870
When he arrived in Japan,

126
00:07:00,870 --> 00:07:02,920
Prince Qing sent his son Zaizhen

127
00:07:03,270 --> 00:07:04,270
to deliver funds.

128
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,600
On the Japanese side,

129
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,560
Duke Ayakura

130
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:08,160
became his guardian,

131
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:09,600
picked out his courses,

132
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:12,000
and introduced him to Japan's upper class.

133
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:13,210
To put it bluntly,

134
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:15,870
they're grooming him for the Qing government

135
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:16,680
as a military leader

136
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,310
who truly understands Japan.

137
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:19,560
If you ask me,

138
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,790
it's not me winning him over.

139
00:07:21,870 --> 00:07:23,270
It's him winning me over.

140
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:25,710
He's trying to win you over?

141
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:26,870
Not just me.

142
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,430
Every Chinese student from his class—

143
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:30,600
whoever's short on cash,

144
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,730
he's offering help.

145
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:34,430
Look at the new prep students—

146
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,390
Yue Kaixian,

147
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,680
Xu Xiaogang,

148
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:37,760
Zhang Xiaozhun,

149
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,159
and Xu Chongzhi—

150
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:41,780
Liang Xiang
is making connections with all of them.

151
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:42,470
Hanhua.

152
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:43,720
I think

153
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,190
it's not you revolutionaries

154
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:46,560
recruiting Liang Xiang.

155
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,490
It's Liang Xiang

156
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,180
recruiting

157
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:50,140
the best of revolutionaries.

158
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,040
Looks like

159
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,720
I underestimated that boy.

160
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:56,600
Of course.

161
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:57,980
Think about it.

162
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,710
A man of the imperial clan

163
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:01,480
actually cut off his braid.

164
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:03,310
Can you name a second royal

165
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:05,120
who's done that?

166
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,820
If that's the case,

167
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,660
here's what you do:

168
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,390
if he's trying to recruit you,

169
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,430
you play along.

170
00:08:15,810 --> 00:08:16,940
Wherever he goes,

171
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,120
you go with him.

172
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,680
I believe he'll need

173
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,740
a trusted right-hand man by his side.

174
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:25,800
You want to...

175
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:26,750
This could be

176
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,880
a once-in-a-lifetime chance
to infiltrate his circle.

177
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:32,559
A perfect strategy for the revolution

178
00:08:33,049 --> 00:08:34,380
to take Beijing one day.

179
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,600
Don't miss it, bro.

180
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:46,850
I'll try my best.

181
00:08:46,870 --> 00:08:49,470
That's not enough.
You have to give it your all.

182
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,030
From now on, don't be distracted

183
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:53,670
by relationships again.

184
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,200
Liang Xiang.

185
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:34,640
This is the library.

186
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,320
No need to salute.

187
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:44,480
[The Conquest of Qing]

188
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:50,270
The Anglo-French Alliance.

189
00:09:51,550 --> 00:09:52,810
The Battle of Beijing.

190
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:55,670
Here's the thing.

191
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:59,550
As a descendant
of the Eight Banners, I've always wondered

192
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:01,550
why the invincible Eight Banners Army

193
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:03,120
collapsed completely

194
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:05,290
after the defeat at Baliqiao.

195
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,000
Good.

196
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:10,910
You know pain,

197
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:16,440
and you're looking for answers in history.

198
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:20,760
It was brutal.

199
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,390
Many of my relatives

200
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:26,010
served under Sengge Rinchen's cavalry.

201
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,870
Tens of thousands of cavalrymen

202
00:10:27,870 --> 00:10:29,550
were slaughtered by the British and French

203
00:10:29,550 --> 00:10:30,870
with their Gatling guns

204
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:32,130
and Congreve rockets.

205
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:34,200
Only a few of them survived.

206
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:36,320
They say

207
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:39,030
when the Empress Dowager heard
so many royals had died,

208
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:40,200
she was deeply shaken.

209
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,360
So she decided they shouldn't fight anymore,

210
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,220
only serve as ceremonial guards.

211
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:49,180
That's no different

212
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,380
from disbanding them.

213
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:53,960
No different at all.

214
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,930
But the worst pain hasn't come yet.

215
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:03,840
Not yet?

216
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:08,440
For China,

217
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:12,720
the most painful moment is still ahead.

218
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:16,130
Only when you've tasted the deepest pain

219
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:17,950
will you learn…

220
00:11:19,710 --> 00:11:21,240
to reflect on it afterward.

221
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,840
Here's goat hair, weasel tail hair,

222
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:49,160
[Shuhong Stationery Store]

223
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,930
badger hair, and squirrel tail hair.

224
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:47,670
This large brush
is for writing big characters.

225
00:11:47,670 --> 00:11:49,800
It's made from horse mane. Take a look.

226
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,200
Brother-in-law.

227
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,180
Tianbai is upstairs.

228
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:53,120
I'm busy here.

229
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,320
You'd also like some ink?

230
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:56,200
If you want ink,

231
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:57,670
get this top-grade ink.

232
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,330
It's good for the brush.

233
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,440
This is Canggui ink.

234
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:02,000
A bit pricier,

235
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,750
but dense and smooth without being sticky.

236
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:06,040
It's easy to write with.

237
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:08,170
Perfect for writing spring couplets.

238
00:12:11,550 --> 00:12:13,960
You and Shuhong
are running a little household now.

239
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:14,440
Hey.

240
00:12:15,130 --> 00:12:16,270
Coffee's over there. Help yourself.

241
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:16,950
Great.

242
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,180
It tastes good.

243
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:27,010
Compared to back in Osaka,

244
00:12:27,260 --> 00:12:28,900
this is heaven.

245
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:32,330
I heard those two bombs

246
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,090
that just went off in Guangzhou

247
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,200
were made by you.

248
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:40,750
How is the merger going?

249
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,320
Don't mention it.

250
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:43,670
It's not that easy.

251
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:44,870
It'll take some time.

252
00:12:47,630 --> 00:12:48,890
Too many differences?

253
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:51,810
How should I put it?

254
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:53,890
Our theoretical goals

255
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:57,000
are miles apart.

256
00:12:57,630 --> 00:12:59,000
Both sides agree that if we don't

257
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,600
overthrow the Qing dynasty,

258
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:01,870
China can't be saved.

259
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:04,170
But as for

260
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:04,870
what kind of country

261
00:13:04,870 --> 00:13:05,960
to build after that

262
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,520
and what system to adopt,

263
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:09,870
that's where all the shouting

264
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,200
and arguments begin.

265
00:13:11,410 --> 00:13:13,540
Why talk about building anything now?

266
00:13:13,550 --> 00:13:15,510
The empire's still holding the reins.

267
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:17,200
Tearing it down is the priority now.

268
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,560
Discussing construction now

269
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,620
only leads to disagreements,

270
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:20,950
making it hard to unite.

271
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:25,560
Tao Chengzhang feels the same way.

272
00:13:26,790 --> 00:13:28,120
But personally, I think

273
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,930
Sun Wen of the Revive China Society

274
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,200
sees further than us.

275
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:35,070
Their theoretical goals

276
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,510
are crystal clear.

277
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,480
Since when did you

278
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,200
side with Sun Wen?

279
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,180
There's an old saying where I'm from—

280
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:45,550
before you jump into the pond,

281
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:47,320
you need to know how to climb back out.

282
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,270
It's easy to tear things down.

283
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:52,360
But after that,

284
00:13:52,510 --> 00:13:53,510
what should we do?

285
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,120
You can't just dive in

286
00:13:55,140 --> 00:13:56,870
without knowing how to get out.

287
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:01,580
Sun Wen's Three Principles of the People

288
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:03,080
are truly brilliant.

289
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:06,150
Land equalization; establishing a republic.

290
00:14:06,630 --> 00:14:07,690
Their destination

291
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:09,750
is very clear.

292
00:14:11,670 --> 00:14:12,200
Right.

293
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,690
We need to keep talking.

294
00:14:16,130 --> 00:14:18,120
When we finally agree on our theoretical

295
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:18,790
goals,

296
00:14:19,710 --> 00:14:21,170
we can talk about merging.

297
00:14:24,890 --> 00:14:25,490
By the way,

298
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:27,550
what exactly is Shuhong up to?

299
00:14:28,140 --> 00:14:29,270
She didn't really come to Tokyo

300
00:14:29,270 --> 00:14:30,930
to do small business, did she?

301
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:34,320
She's got her whole heart

302
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,850
set on that shop of hers now,

303
00:14:35,870 --> 00:14:37,470
earning every penny she can.

304
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:41,130
Let me tell you something.

305
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,990
Let her help you buy weapons.

306
00:14:45,890 --> 00:14:46,680
What?

307
00:14:48,050 --> 00:14:49,960
You want her to help me buy weapons?

308
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:52,290
She's got a low profile—perfect for this.

309
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:53,750
Of course,

310
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:54,630
this is

311
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:56,870
a last resort.

312
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:05,630
What?

313
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:07,730
You want me to buy weapons for you?

314
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:09,360
You want me to buy rifles?

315
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:13,000
Don't think of them as rifles.

316
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,200
Just think of them as…

317
00:15:14,670 --> 00:15:16,670
celery, cabbage, and eggs.

318
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:17,790
Just a vegetable dealer.

319
00:15:17,790 --> 00:15:19,000
This way, it won't weigh on you.

320
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,120
How's that the same?

321
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,780
Those things can kill people!

322
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,670
Don't put it like that.

323
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:24,510
If you're set on it,

324
00:15:24,510 --> 00:15:26,370
even chopsticks can kill people.

325
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:29,640
Let me ask you.

326
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:31,850
Haven't you guys done this before?

327
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:33,670
Then let him keep doing it.

328
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:34,750
Why drag me in?

329
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,200
Because you're capable.

330
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,400
Don't sweet-talk me.

331
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:41,790
Who's paying?

332
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,200
We've raised

333
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,400
a donation overseas.

334
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,130
So you do have money.

335
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:48,700
Money is not a problem.

336
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,590
Then why stop the old supply chain?

337
00:15:56,150 --> 00:15:57,350
Right now, relations

338
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:59,440
between Japan and Russia are tense.

339
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,060
Japan needs China,

340
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:03,200
so they're trying hard to please the court.

341
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,320
All the things

342
00:16:04,550 --> 00:16:05,670
revolutionaries used to

343
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:07,200
get away with in Japan—

344
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:09,240
now they've cracked down on them.

345
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:10,640
Every channel is cut off,

346
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:12,840
and everyone's under surveillance.

347
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,440
That's why we need your help.

348
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:17,870
Besides, it's easier for women
to move around unnoticed.

349
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,790
Fine, I'll give it a try.

350
00:16:24,630 --> 00:16:25,550
Have them deposit the money

351
00:16:25,550 --> 00:16:26,950
into the shop's account.

352
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,270
Don't short me again.

353
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,260
Integrity is important in business.

354
00:16:31,670 --> 00:16:32,430
Hold on,

355
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:33,740
you're saying yes?

356
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:37,000
Didn't you want me to say yes?

357
00:16:37,370 --> 00:16:38,870
But that was way too easy.

358
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:40,900
You just bought into this?

359
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:41,750
Well…

360
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:44,050
how could I not trust you two?

361
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:45,580
That's my brother-in-law.

362
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:47,190
Are you my nemesis?

363
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:52,200
See? This is why you're naive.

364
00:16:53,190 --> 00:16:55,370
Let me tell you how you should handle this.

365
00:16:55,370 --> 00:16:56,410
I'm all ears.

366
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:58,720
Even if you agree,

367
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,650
you've got to negotiate with them.

368
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:01,480
First,

369
00:17:03,380 --> 00:17:05,440
you don't handle the money directly.

370
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:08,720
The accounts
among revolutionaries are a mess.

371
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:11,240
Not everyone
is a selfless saint.

372
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:13,960
Some are just
getting rich off this revolution.

373
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:15,720
Keep your hands off the cash.

374
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:17,960
Arrange the ships and goods,

375
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,220
negotiate the prices,

376
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:21,579
but let them handle the payments.

377
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:23,310
Second,

378
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,069
you need to find a firearm expert.

379
00:17:29,670 --> 00:17:31,270
Tokyo's full of con artists.

380
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:32,830
They may hand you a steel pipe

381
00:17:32,830 --> 00:17:33,720
and call it a rifle.

382
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,750
Don't be fooled.

383
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:38,000
You need an expert
to inspect the guns for you.

384
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,480
You need to know the prices

385
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,630
for different guns.

386
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:44,830
You're an expert.

387
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:46,350
Why don't I just hire you?

388
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:47,310
Absolutely not!

389
00:17:47,350 --> 00:17:48,350
I'm a revolutionary leader,

390
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:49,350
not your errand boy.

391
00:17:49,350 --> 00:17:50,590
Stop bragging.

392
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,640
In the past several years,

393
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:54,350
what exactly have you led?

394
00:17:54,350 --> 00:17:55,880
Name one thing you've actually achieved.

395
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,720
Revolution takes time.

396
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,980
Don't you understand?

397
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,250
What I, Wu Tianbai, promote

398
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:02,590
is spirit.

399
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:04,620
What China needs most right now

400
00:18:04,620 --> 00:18:05,950
is revolutionary spirit!

401
00:18:05,950 --> 00:18:07,480
Just keep being all spirit.

402
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:09,000
I can buy guns for you,

403
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,200
but I've got one condition.

404
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,750
Otherwise, I'm not doing it.

405
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:12,310
Say it.

406
00:18:14,890 --> 00:18:16,150
You have to work for me.

407
00:18:28,870 --> 00:18:31,520
Do you know why Duke Ayakura called for me?

408
00:18:31,550 --> 00:18:33,350
I don't know.

409
00:18:42,770 --> 00:18:44,740
[Shuhong Stationery Store]

410
00:19:05,140 --> 00:19:10,090
[Duke Ayakura's residence]

411
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,450
Liang Xiang.

412
00:19:41,960 --> 00:19:44,350
Why are you here so early?

413
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:46,000
I'm not sure myself.

414
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,480
What a beautiful dog.

415
00:19:49,830 --> 00:19:50,890
Does it have a name?

416
00:19:51,070 --> 00:19:51,830
Onion.

417
00:19:53,070 --> 00:19:53,960
Interesting.

418
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:57,240
Most people's onions grow in the soil.

419
00:19:57,750 --> 00:20:01,070
Yours runs around on four legs.

420
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:01,960
Does it bite?

421
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:07,210
I can't have a proper conversation
with someone who doesn't understand dogs.

422
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,350
When I was five,

423
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,960
I had a dog too.

424
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:16,670
I named it Chubby.

425
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,830
But three years later,

426
00:20:19,350 --> 00:20:22,350
it was so skinny it was all bones.

427
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,330
Lieutenant Hirata came by yesterday.

428
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:28,070
What for?

429
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,240
He proposed to me.

430
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:36,350
Really?

431
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:39,830
This dog's great.

432
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:42,680
How often do you bathe it?

433
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:47,730
Why are you avoiding it?

434
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:51,920
Avoiding?

435
00:20:52,510 --> 00:20:53,160
Me?

436
00:20:55,310 --> 00:20:56,480
Why don't you ask me

437
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:58,110
how I answered him?

438
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:03,240
I'm not your minister of justice, am I?

439
00:21:06,610 --> 00:21:07,610
I said yes.

440
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:08,960
But

441
00:21:09,670 --> 00:21:10,950
on one condition.

442
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:16,600
You made him promise
to get promoted to captain first?

443
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,750
How did you know?

444
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:21,960
My goodness, I was right?

445
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,460
I just can't stand the idea

446
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,440
that the man I'll marry

447
00:21:28,910 --> 00:21:30,040
has to keep saluting

448
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,750
when he meets my childhood friend.

449
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,910
Duke asks you to join him inside.

450
00:21:34,590 --> 00:21:35,110
Yes.

451
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:08,960
You came.

452
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,320
Yes, I've been here for a bit.

453
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,310
Come over here.

454
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,590
See this? Port Arthur.

455
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,080
Yes, I see it.

456
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:31,590
Just yesterday,

457
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:34,450
the Japanese Combined Fleet,

458
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:37,720
led by Togo Heihachiro,

459
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:40,230
launched a surprise attack

460
00:22:40,830 --> 00:22:44,030
on the Russian Pacific Squadron
anchored at Port Arthur.

461
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,880
The war broke out.

462
00:22:51,140 --> 00:22:51,930
You mean

463
00:22:52,590 --> 00:22:55,160
the Japanese and Russian armies

464
00:22:55,650 --> 00:22:58,760
have started fighting on China's

465
00:22:58,790 --> 00:22:59,990
Liaodong Peninsula?

466
00:23:02,230 --> 00:23:03,750
That's how it looks to you.

467
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:22,110
Let me give you a question

468
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:23,720
to think about.

469
00:23:25,350 --> 00:23:26,240
Go ahead.

470
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:28,510
Liang Xiang,

471
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:32,590
imagine you're Yuan Shikai right now.

472
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:36,510
You control all of the Qing dynasty's

473
00:23:36,510 --> 00:23:38,590
elite forces.

474
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:41,480
How would you respond

475
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:43,550
to what happened yesterday?

476
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,880
What's going on? Did something happen?

477
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,110
Didn't you notice?

478
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:02,590
Starting today, all Japanese students
have stopped attending classes.

479
00:24:02,590 --> 00:24:04,590
Only we Chinese students are still in class.

480
00:24:04,590 --> 00:24:05,480
Why?

481
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:06,830
No idea.

482
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:09,000
I saw the Japanese cadets
getting issued boots

483
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:09,930
and canned food.

484
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:11,750
That's strange…

485
00:24:11,790 --> 00:24:13,070
Why the canned food?

486
00:24:21,790 --> 00:24:22,720
Take your seats.

487
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:26,590
Class begins.

488
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:31,070
In field conditions,

489
00:24:32,830 --> 00:24:33,550
infantry

490
00:24:35,110 --> 00:24:35,960
squadron…

491
00:24:37,590 --> 00:24:38,960
Do you think Hirata knows?

492
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:40,640
defense.

493
00:24:39,650 --> 00:24:42,220
[Infantry Squadron Defense]

494
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:48,880
Cadet Kaizhi.

495
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:51,880
Do you have any thoughts

496
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:54,960
you'd like to share with the class?

497
00:24:59,590 --> 00:25:00,200
Sir,

498
00:25:01,110 --> 00:25:02,240
we're all wondering

499
00:25:02,550 --> 00:25:04,150
why our Japanese classmates

500
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:07,960
stopped attending classes.

501
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,700
To sum it up in one word,

502
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:15,590
that is…

503
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:18,400
war.

504
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:30,590
They're graduating early

505
00:25:30,790 --> 00:25:33,070
and heading straight to the front lines.

506
00:25:34,830 --> 00:25:36,070
The war

507
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:39,350
needs them now.

508
00:25:48,070 --> 00:25:50,020
Until we receive further orders,

509
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,200
we

510
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,960
will continue with our lessons.

511
00:25:59,790 --> 00:26:01,200
In the Japanese army,

512
00:26:00,020 --> 00:26:07,560
[They launched a surprise attack on the Russian fleet stationed at China's Port Arthur. The Russo-Japanese War began.]

513
00:26:00,020 --> 00:26:07,560
[On the 29th year, 12th month, and 23rd day of the Guangxu reign—February 8th, 1904—the Imperial Japanese Navy officially declared war.]

514
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:04,590
the infantry squadron is the most basic

515
00:26:04,790 --> 00:26:06,720
small-scale combat unit.

516
00:26:13,350 --> 00:26:14,280
Where did you go?

517
00:26:14,410 --> 00:26:16,010
Something big has happened.

518
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:17,830
Tufang,

519
00:26:19,070 --> 00:26:20,310
the Japanese Third Army

520
00:26:20,310 --> 00:26:21,350
is about to set out

521
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:23,260
for the Liaodong Peninsula.

522
00:26:23,260 --> 00:26:24,460
You heard something?

523
00:26:24,530 --> 00:26:25,420
What I heard

524
00:26:26,110 --> 00:26:27,510
is already in the papers.

525
00:26:28,610 --> 00:26:29,480
Take a look.

526
00:26:46,350 --> 00:26:47,350
What the heck?

527
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:48,350
It's like two sumo giants

528
00:26:48,350 --> 00:26:49,440
deciding to fight in your house,

529
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:51,100
smashing everything to bits.

530
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,400
If they win, they win;

531
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:54,350
if they lose,
we're left to clean up the mess.

532
00:26:54,350 --> 00:26:55,810
Tufang, that's so unfair!

533
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,020
Have you read this?

534
00:26:57,830 --> 00:26:59,000
Look at the front page.

535
00:26:59,000 --> 00:26:59,680
Shut up.

536
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:00,830
Give me a break.

537
00:27:01,110 --> 00:27:02,000
Stop yapping.

538
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:04,140
You're like an old housewife.

539
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:05,510
If you don't like sumo,

540
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:07,350
show them some Chinese kung fu.

541
00:27:07,350 --> 00:27:09,200
What's all this blabbering good for?

542
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:09,720
You think

543
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:10,200
you're a bird?

544
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:11,600
Chattering all the time.

545
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:12,930
Does it work?

546
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,550
If it doesn't, shut up.

547
00:27:15,610 --> 00:27:16,680
So annoying.

548
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:19,080
Why throw a tantrum at me?

549
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,700
I say, Qianli,

550
00:27:28,070 --> 00:27:29,550
you're a real man

551
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,490
with a rare patriotic soul.

552
00:27:32,590 --> 00:27:33,440
Of course.

553
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:35,120
Not saying you're wrong,

554
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:37,310
but you don't think around corners.

555
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,440
What are we here for?

556
00:27:38,830 --> 00:27:40,960
We're here to study military affairs.

557
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:42,200
So think about it.

558
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:43,740
With a war going on,

559
00:27:44,310 --> 00:27:46,110
isn't this the perfect time for us to learn?

560
00:27:46,110 --> 00:27:47,200
All those tricks

561
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:49,040
they'd normally never teach us—

562
00:27:49,270 --> 00:27:51,090
now they have no choice but to reveal them.

563
00:27:51,090 --> 00:27:51,680
This time,

564
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:53,540
Togo Heihachiro's naval ambush—

565
00:27:53,670 --> 00:27:55,000
is it the same tactic they used

566
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:56,200
against our Beiyang Fleet

567
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,360
during the Sino-Japanese War?

568
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:58,470
Exactly the same.

569
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:01,800
The war's started,
and it's about to escalate.

570
00:28:01,830 --> 00:28:03,310
Let's just watch how these Japanese

571
00:28:03,310 --> 00:28:05,830
mobilize their troops and move their armies.

572
00:28:05,830 --> 00:28:07,720
They'll have to use

573
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:10,620
all their new weapons
and tactics, won't they?

574
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,610
It was easy for them to fight us,

575
00:28:13,830 --> 00:28:16,590
but going up against
the Russians won't be so easy.

576
00:28:16,590 --> 00:28:17,650
Because it's hard,

