00:28:17,780 --> 00:28:18,690
they'll have to throw in

578
00:28:18,690 --> 00:28:20,090
everything they've got.

579
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:20,960
And us?

580
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:22,680
Amateurs watch the excitement,

581
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,410
but pros watch the techniques.

582
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:27,210
Isn't that exactly what we're here to learn?

583
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:28,480
Right.

584
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,220
Isn't that so, Tufang?

585
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:36,560
So you're the only wise man here.

586
00:28:51,650 --> 00:28:54,520
The guns are a bit outdated,

587
00:28:56,630 --> 00:28:58,260
decommissioned

588
00:28:58,350 --> 00:28:59,240
by the army

589
00:29:00,870 --> 00:29:02,110
five years ago.

590
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:05,170
But they've been well maintained.

591
00:29:06,860 --> 00:29:09,100
Each one's coated with butter

592
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:12,340
and wrapped individually

593
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:14,830
in oilcloth.

594
00:29:16,370 --> 00:29:17,440
Don't just talk.

595
00:29:18,190 --> 00:29:19,800
I need to check them myself.

596
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:26,480
You pay,

597
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:30,080
and you can
get your hands on them immediately.

598
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:33,590
Take them back to China.

599
00:29:34,550 --> 00:29:37,590
They're better than the stuff your army

600
00:29:38,830 --> 00:29:39,960
is currently using.

601
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:48,080
Don't try to fool me.

602
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:50,530
The Beiyang Army's three divisions

603
00:29:50,530 --> 00:29:52,140
all use Mannlicher rifles,

604
00:29:52,500 --> 00:29:54,960
carbines, pistols, and Krupp cannons.

605
00:29:56,830 --> 00:29:58,070
You're actually asking 100 yen a piece

606
00:29:58,070 --> 00:29:59,670
for this second-hand stuff?

607
00:30:03,830 --> 00:30:05,830
You really are an expert.

608
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,070
If I can't handle the heat,

609
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:10,000
I wouldn't be playing with fire.

610
00:30:11,110 --> 00:30:12,110
We can…

611
00:30:13,350 --> 00:30:14,830
negotiate the price.

612
00:30:37,110 --> 00:30:38,110
What's going on?

613
00:30:38,590 --> 00:30:39,790
Why are you so angry?

614
00:30:40,070 --> 00:30:42,260
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven.

615
00:30:42,260 --> 00:30:43,390
What does that mean?

616
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:44,920
A bunch of fools!

617
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:47,860
They can't even count past seven.

618
00:30:48,590 --> 00:30:49,480
Who do you mean?

619
00:30:50,070 --> 00:30:50,550
The Qing government

620
00:30:50,550 --> 00:30:52,910
has made its stance
on the Russo-Japanese War.

621
00:30:52,910 --> 00:30:53,970
You know what it is?

622
00:30:54,550 --> 00:30:55,610
Strictly neutral.

623
00:30:56,350 --> 00:30:57,830
Aren't they just a bunch of fools?

624
00:30:57,830 --> 00:30:58,960
Completely rotten!

625
00:30:59,830 --> 00:31:00,830
That's good.

626
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:03,160
It means tearing it down is easy.

627
00:31:04,260 --> 00:31:05,040
I saw those

628
00:31:05,070 --> 00:31:05,960
Japanese soldiers

629
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:07,200
about to head off to the front lines,

630
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:10,000
every one of them
ready to die without hesitation.

631
00:31:10,550 --> 00:31:12,070
I just hate it!

632
00:31:14,310 --> 00:31:15,070
Hate what?

633
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:17,850
Hate that we don't have such soldiers!

634
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,650
We've got 400 million people in China, but…

635
00:31:19,650 --> 00:31:21,330
Stop lecturing me.

636
00:31:21,770 --> 00:31:23,040
Just tell me,

637
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:25,280
did you get the price down or not?

638
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:27,710
Kanyama softened up.

639
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:29,580
How much is he willing to lower it?

640
00:31:29,580 --> 00:31:30,710
Five yen off per gun.

641
00:31:31,350 --> 00:31:32,350
Five's not enough.

642
00:31:32,350 --> 00:31:34,080
At least knock another ten off.

643
00:31:36,830 --> 00:31:38,070
For heaven's sake,

644
00:31:38,190 --> 00:31:38,880
do you even know

645
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:40,070
what it's like out there now?

646
00:31:40,070 --> 00:31:41,200
War is coming.

647
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:42,680
What will be the most valuable?

648
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:43,720
Guns.

649
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:45,590
Finding a seller at all is already lucky,

650
00:31:45,590 --> 00:31:47,190
and you're trying to haggle?

651
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:48,590
You think I'm an idiot?

652
00:31:48,590 --> 00:31:49,070
I...

653
00:31:49,350 --> 00:31:50,480
Because of the war,

654
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:51,830
guns are worthless.

655
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:53,590
When there's war,

656
00:31:53,590 --> 00:31:54,590
arms factories go full throttle,

657
00:31:54,590 --> 00:31:55,850
working day and night.

658
00:31:56,110 --> 00:31:56,960
When there's war,

659
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:58,560
weapons will be everywhere!

660
00:31:58,830 --> 00:31:59,830
The more guns,

661
00:32:00,410 --> 00:32:01,740
the looser the control.

662
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:05,400
Just wait till thousands of people die.

663
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:07,320
There'll be even more guns.

664
00:32:08,290 --> 00:32:09,490
You don't believe me?

665
00:32:09,890 --> 00:32:10,960
Just wait and see.

666
00:32:11,150 --> 00:32:13,080
And those second-hand guns of his?

667
00:32:13,220 --> 00:32:13,790
Haggle!

668
00:32:14,120 --> 00:32:16,150
Ten yen off is me being generous.

669
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,840
Why are you looking at me?

670
00:32:23,550 --> 00:32:25,350
I didn't know you were so clever.

671
00:32:35,310 --> 00:32:36,100
Wu Tianbai!

672
00:32:40,350 --> 00:32:41,280
No one

673
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:46,130
[Tokyo Imperial University]

674
00:32:41,830 --> 00:32:42,960
has the power

675
00:32:43,590 --> 00:32:45,960
to keep us chained in slavery forever.

676
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,600
And no so-called destiny

677
00:32:49,660 --> 00:32:50,490
can condemn

678
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,920
our country to permanent humiliation.

679
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:54,590
Not Tsarist Russia.

680
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,110
Not Japanese warlords!

681
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,230
Exactly!

682
00:33:04,710 --> 00:33:06,320
We must have a goal.

683
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,000
We must have

684
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:10,070
a simple and clear goal.

685
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:11,720
It's too important.

686
00:33:12,070 --> 00:33:13,480
With it, we find stability.

687
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,200
Without it, we fall into danger.

688
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:16,160
Today's China

689
00:33:16,540 --> 00:33:18,300
could rise or fall,

690
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:20,320
grow strong or stay weak,

691
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:21,940
splinter or unite.

692
00:33:22,650 --> 00:33:23,590
We're already

693
00:33:23,590 --> 00:33:24,790
at a crossroads.

694
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:26,410
Where do we go from here?

695
00:33:26,710 --> 00:33:28,880
Where is our country headed?

696
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,940
It comes back to that goal,

697
00:33:31,110 --> 00:33:32,310
the goal we fight for.

698
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,280
Do you have it?

699
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:37,790
Yes! Yes! Yes!

700
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,270
What's the goal

701
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:40,900
you're talking about?

702
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:45,960
I know you, young man.

703
00:33:46,550 --> 00:33:47,400
I know you support

704
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:48,880
reform within the court.

705
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,120
Some believe imperialism

706
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:52,960
has been China's long-term enemy,

707
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:53,640
and I agree

708
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,080
with that view.

709
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:57,400
It's well-founded.

710
00:33:57,960 --> 00:33:59,370
But it also brings us a problem

711
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:00,890
we can't solve.

712
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:05,570
Before we gain control of state power,

713
00:34:06,070 --> 00:34:07,070
how will we stand up

714
00:34:07,070 --> 00:34:08,630
to the foreign powers?

715
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:11,000
Just by standing here

716
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:12,190
with empty talk?

717
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,190
That's why the only goal

718
00:34:14,190 --> 00:34:15,090
I'm pointing you toward

719
00:34:15,090 --> 00:34:16,300
is revolution!

720
00:34:16,340 --> 00:34:17,340
With revolution,

721
00:34:17,510 --> 00:34:19,150
we'll bury the Qing dynasty!

722
00:34:19,630 --> 00:34:21,360
Revolution is the only way out!

723
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:22,320
Great!

724
00:34:24,110 --> 00:34:24,840
Revolution!

725
00:34:24,860 --> 00:34:29,090
Revolution! Revolution!

726
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:30,150
Revolution!

727
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:32,960
Revolution! Revolution!

728
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:33,840
Revolution!

729
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:35,630
Revolution!

730
00:34:35,630 --> 00:34:36,840
Great!

731
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:37,630
Revolution!

732
00:34:37,630 --> 00:34:39,400
Great!

733
00:34:41,710 --> 00:34:43,480
Great!

734
00:34:41,969 --> 00:34:47,300
[his beliefs are irreconcilable with theirs, and a fierce fight is bound to come.]

735
00:34:41,969 --> 00:34:47,300
[Liang Xiang resolves to dedicate himself to military studies and help the court recruit new talent. At last, he realizes]

736
00:34:41,969 --> 00:34:47,300
[The Russo-Japanese War rages on, stirring the hearts of all Chinese. Cries for revolution echo everywhere.]

737
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:48,320
Revolution! Revolution!

738
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,190
Revolution!

739
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:52,550
Revolution! Revolution!

740
00:34:58,310 --> 00:34:59,270
Yang Kaizhi!

741
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:16,480
Let's go.

742
00:35:17,650 --> 00:35:19,520
Kaizhi! Kaizhi!

743
00:35:33,010 --> 00:35:34,400
I can't run anymore.

744
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:35,670
I'll pull you along!

745
00:35:36,550 --> 00:35:39,320
I really can't run anymore.

746
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,400
Didn't you hear the commotion back there?

747
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,070
The police will be here any second.

748
00:35:43,070 --> 00:35:44,550
Are you afraid of the police?

749
00:35:44,550 --> 00:35:45,860
I'm not afraid of them!

750
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:48,360
We can't let the police find out.

751
00:35:53,150 --> 00:35:54,070
Are you afraid?

752
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,960
I'm afraid they'll disturb us.

753
00:35:57,440 --> 00:35:58,230
Stop.

754
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:00,850
I really can't run anymore.

755
00:36:06,070 --> 00:36:06,800
I...

756
00:36:08,830 --> 00:36:10,310
I'm already

757
00:36:11,510 --> 00:36:12,880
engaged.

758
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:15,150
Since when?

759
00:36:15,710 --> 00:36:19,070
You never told me.

760
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:21,010
Just yesterday.

761
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:24,770
They arranged it for me.

762
00:36:27,330 --> 00:36:28,400
Arranged it?

763
00:36:34,190 --> 00:36:35,110
Tell me,

764
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:39,960
who are they? Who exactly are they?

765
00:36:43,690 --> 00:36:45,610
Japan's Security Police.

766
00:36:55,990 --> 00:36:56,840
What's wrong?

767
00:36:57,920 --> 00:36:59,440
Are you afraid of them?

768
00:37:01,210 --> 00:37:02,160
You agreed to it?

769
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:06,810
You think I had a choice?

770
00:37:07,710 --> 00:37:09,910
And you're going to accept it like that?

771
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,860
It's because I refuse to accept it

772
00:37:12,710 --> 00:37:14,480
that I came to you!

773
00:37:15,230 --> 00:37:16,510
Take me away.

774
00:37:17,110 --> 00:37:19,150
Let's run off together!

775
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,040
Let me think.

776
00:37:31,900 --> 00:37:32,900
I need to think.

777
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:34,720
Think about what?

778
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:36,960
There's no time left!

779
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,780
Let's head for the dock now

780
00:37:40,760 --> 00:37:42,160
and go to China together!

781
00:37:43,050 --> 00:37:44,090
But

782
00:37:44,590 --> 00:37:46,840
if I leave like this,

783
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:49,850
I'll never be able to come back.

784
00:37:50,190 --> 00:37:51,450
Let's think it through

785
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:54,840
and see if there's a better way.

786
00:38:02,710 --> 00:38:05,400
I still have my revolution in Tokyo.

787
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:07,190
If I take you away,

788
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:08,030
then…

789
00:38:08,340 --> 00:38:10,740
Revolution and love are the same thing!

790
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:14,320
A revolutionary is always a romantic.

791
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:16,740
Please.

792
00:38:16,770 --> 00:38:17,760
Please, take me away.

793
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,540
They're not the same.

794
00:38:19,570 --> 00:38:20,410
Really.

795
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:24,070
Don't look at me like that.

796
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:27,000
Revolution demands sacrifice.

797
00:38:27,230 --> 00:38:28,760
Right now, I can't…

798
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:39,770
I understand.

799
00:38:40,970 --> 00:38:41,970
You never really…

800
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:48,670
You never really understood me.

801
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:58,370
It's too late for everything.

802
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,000
See?

803
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:02,990
Your chance is gone.

804
00:39:03,590 --> 00:39:05,550
You missed it.

805
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:08,670
They're coming this way.

806
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:15,580
Why do we have to keep watching

807
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:18,590
that Korean woman every day?

808
00:39:19,030 --> 00:39:20,590
It's exhausting.

809
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:24,230
It's an order from above.

810
00:39:24,250 --> 00:39:25,730
Her father

811
00:39:26,030 --> 00:39:28,440
is an anti-Japanese activist.

812
00:39:54,550 --> 00:39:56,000
Please come again.

813
00:40:00,390 --> 00:40:03,090
[Shuhong Stationery Store]

814
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:32,920
You're not

815
00:40:33,620 --> 00:40:35,550
here for paintings again, are you?

816
00:40:37,170 --> 00:40:38,650
I'm not buying anything.

817
00:40:40,950 --> 00:40:41,790
Then you...

818
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:43,440
L-Last time,

819
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,370
I passed by your shop in a carriage.

820
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:46,800
So…

821
00:40:49,130 --> 00:40:51,010
can I… can I treat you to a meal?

822
00:40:52,580 --> 00:40:53,460
You want to…

823
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:54,720
buy me dinner?

824
00:40:54,980 --> 00:40:56,020
I just ate.

825
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:04,030
Well…

826
00:41:04,550 --> 00:41:05,190
Alright.

827
00:41:07,620 --> 00:41:09,280
Maybe wait for me outside for a bit?

828
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:10,400
Look at me, dressed like this.

829
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:12,330
I'll change into something nicer.

830
00:41:12,830 --> 00:41:13,350
Alright.
